comment: Joseph (TOR) has his arms extended when Ginobili (SAS) "rips thru" and a personal foul is correctly called for the contact to the arm. Since the contact occurred on the side to side motion it is not considered a shooting foul.
Aldridge (SAS) establishes a legal guarding position and jumps vertically as he legally contests DeRozan's (TOR) driving shot attempt.
LATR shows that Leonard (SAS) cleanly strips the ball from Lowry (TOR) and that the contact by Parker (SAS) after the ball is loose is considered incidental.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that the ball was last touched by Leonard (SAS) was overturned. San Antonio was awarded possession.
Aldridge (SAS) sets the screen on Patterson (TOR) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Biyombo (TOR) and Aldridge (SAS) make incidental contact with one another during rebounding that does not affect the putback dunk attempt.
Biyombo (TOR) firms up as he sets the screen on Green (SAS) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Aldridge (SAS) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Lowry's (TOR) drive and shot attempt.
Lowry (TOR) makes incidental contact with Aldridge (SAS) during rebounding.
Ginobili (SAS) commits a take foul on DeRozan (TOR).
